 that can trigger sudden interest rate spikes.
 When calibrated to the Argentine economy,
 the model not only matches the high average sovereign spread observed in the data a challenge for the standard model but also endogenously generates excess volatility in interest rates and a more fragile financial environment characterized by higher equilibrium debt and default rates.
 
\end_layout

